node.text: Victoria gets REAL with me about her experience with binge eating, body image, and how being a college athlete can take a toll on your mental health. We talk about how she dealt with these challenges and her pathway to therapy and the help we all need from time to time. We end with some tips for performing under pressure, so you don’t want to miss that! My hope is that you all walk away with something that will help you improve your own mental health and remember you are NEVER alone!

node.title: Body Image, Mental Health & More with Victoria Garrick!

node.text: I had a little time on my hands today so I scrolled through my camera roll and threw together this video🤗 Grateful for all these times and these humans and can’t wait to make more memories! ❤️ @alixklineman @jenniferkessy & * @fiapogtenius we need some video with you! 🙈

I wouldn’t be where I am today had it not been for the time I was able to spend with my mom, Margie. She’s who I am #RelentlessFor, and why time is so precious to me. And today with @verzenio, more time is possible for certain people living with HR+, HER2- metastatic breast cancer.

Verzenio was proven to help women with HR+, HER2- metastatic breast cancer live significantly longer. In a clinical study, women taking Verzenio + fulvestrant lived for a median of 46.7 months vs. 37.3 months on fulvestrant alone. In the same study, Verzenio + fulvestrant delayed cancer growth for a median of 16.4 months vs 9.3 months on fulvestrant alone.

Margie Ross was not a Verzenio patient.

Alix and I have been using Tonal for some of our strength training and it’s amazing. This was my first time ever lifting with digital weight🤯 and I was shocked at how efficient while challenging the workout was!💪🏼 I love that Tonal tracks my reps and volume, so I know exactly what I‘ve done after every training session. And the best part is it fits in my house!! 🤩 I can’t wait to keep using it to get stronger and to push myself with this new technology.👊🏼
#BeYourStrongest #PoweredByTonal #ATeam

The last few days here in Tokyo have been super busy preparing for competition to start! Lots of training, lots of recovery, lots of food, and lots of excitement! (And definitely lots of pin trading 🤗) 

This morning we got to practice on center court with our fellow Americans, the stadium is beautiful 😍 And we had to make the very tough decision of which color combos ❤️🤍💙 in our competition suits we were going to name our first, second, and third choices- any guesses?
